Ordering

Ordering  How to Contact Customer Care Ordering by Phone, Fax or Mail Requesting a CD-ROM Catalog Safe-Shopping Guarantee Setting Up an Online Account Lost Your Password? Special Offers & Promotional Codes Worldwide Shipping Tax-Exempt Customers   How to Contact Customer Care  Customers who wish to: order products; make inquiries concerning orders already placed; request  title information, price, availability, or general bibliographic data; or establish a new account should contact our Customer Care Department at:  Customer Care Center - Consumer Accounts 10475 Crosspoint Blvd. Indianapolis, IN  46256 Phone: (877) 762-2974 Fax: (800) 597-3299 Web: http://support.wiley.com  Hours: Weekdays, 8:00 A.M. to 8:00 P.M. Eastern Time  Customers who wish to contact Customer Care regarding Journals, please  visit our Journal Subscriptions section.  Customers who wish to contact Customer Care concerning their Trade or Reseller  Accounts, please visit our Resources for Booksellers section. Establishing/Increasing a Credit Line for Customer Purchases:
A completed Credit Application, PDF (75 KB), is required for all Customers seeking a credit line for purchases in excess of $20,000 for either a new or existing account. For those seeking an extension of credit greater than $25,000, financial statements are also requested. Your completed Credit Application may be returned via email to CreditRiskDept@wiley.com or via fax to 732-302-2332 Attn: Credit Risk Dept.
Questions regarding payment of invoices on existing accounts may be directed to 1-800-758-9477 where you will be routed to your credit representative or you may fax your inquiry to 1-732-302-2201.
Ordering by Phone, Fax or Mail  Wiley products may be ordered directly from the address and phone numbers shown below.  We accept payment by check, money order, or credit card. We accept American Express,  Visa, and Mastercard. Checks and money orders must be drawn on a U.S. bank. Customers with an existing Wiley account number who wish to place telephone orders should have  their account numbers readily available when they call.   Customer Care Center - Consumer Accounts 10475 Crosspoint Blvd. Indianapolis, IN  46256 Phone: (877) 762-2974 Fax: (800) 597-3299 Hours: Weekdays, 8:00 A.M. to 8:00 P.M. Eastern Time  Customers interested in purchasing Journals, please visit our Journal Subscriptions section for ordering information.

 Requesting a Wiley Catalog on CD-ROM  If you would like to receive a copy of the Wiley catalog on CD-ROM send an e-mail to fmcdermo@wiley.com.  Please include your name, address, and phone number in the body of the e-mail. Supply is limited.

 Safe-Shopping Guarantee  When you use your credit card to shop at wiley.com, rest assured that the transaction is secure. Our servers use Secure Sockets Layer (SSL), an advanced encryption technology–the Internet standard for secure transactions. This  technology safeguards your personal information and guarantees privacy.  Your order information and purchase history are further protected by a  password you choose. If you forget your password, we will first verify  your identity, then e-mail you a new password.

 Setting Up an Online Account  You are invited to establish a personal account when you make a purchase on this site.  Establishing an account will enable you to track recent  orders, view your order history, and keep your basic account information up to date.  After completing your check out process, all you have to do is select a password and your account will be ready to go. Then you will be able to access your account information at any time by clicking on the My Account link located in the top left-hand corner of most pages on this site.

 Lost Your Password?  If you've lost or forgotten the password for your Wiley account, we can  send you a new one. Anywhere you’re asked to provide a password,  there will be a link to our Password Retrieval page. Just click on the  link, fill out the form, and submit. We'll immediately generate a new  password and e-mail it to the address we have in your account record.

 Special Offers & Promotional Codes  You will find promotional (or discount) codes on Wiley mailings, in our e-mail campaigns, and at conferences where Wiley is an exhibitor. If you have a code to apply towards your online purchase, please enter the code in the Promotion/Discount  Information field in your shopping cart. You also may use a code when placing a mail,  fax, or phone order.

 Worldwide Shipping  wiley.com services most countries around the world.  Special instructions apply  when shipping to the following locations: Special instructions when shipping to: Germany, Austria, Switzerland,  Luxembourg, Liechtenstein  Website: www.wiley-vch.de  Wiley-VCH Verlag GmbH Customer Service Department P.O. Box 101161 D-69451 Weinheim Germany  Phone: +49 6201 606152 Fax: +49 6201 606184 E-mail: sales-books@wiley-vch.de

 Tax-Exempt Customers  To take advantage of your tax-exempt status when you place an order with Wiley, you will need to  furnish certain documentation. To expedite this process, we ask that you contact Customer Care  directly by telephone at (877) 762-2974 weekdays between 8 A.M. and 8 P.M. Eastern Time, or  through our Website at http://support.wiley.com, to place your order.   If you are an employee of the US Government and are placing an order using an Impact credit card, you may place a tax-exempt order online through the Wiley Resources for Government website at http://www.wiley.com/gov.  You will  also receive the benefit of GSA discounts and free shipping.

 









